n's%20former%20prime%20minister%2C%20launched%20a%20campaign%20of%20%26quot%3BAbenomics%26quot%3B%20that%20included%20massive%20stimulus%20packages%20designed%20to%20inspire%20business%20and%20household%20spending.%20After%20all%20this%20hard%20work%2C%20Japan%20is%20starting%20to%20show%20signs%20that%20better%20days%20are%20ahead.%20Koo%20says%20executive%20culture%20is%20shifting%20toward%20more%20of%20an%20appetite%20for%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20more%20risk%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20means%20more%20investment%20in%20new%20projects.%20He%20compared%20the%20C-suite's%20caution%20to%20the%20skepticism%20Americans%20who%20lived%20through%20the%20Great%20Depression%20in%20the%201930s%20felt%20toward%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20a%20form%20of%20PTSD.%20But%2C%20slowly%2C%20things%20are%20changing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20a%20good%20sign%2C%26quot%3B%20Koo%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20Japanese%20are%20very%20cautious%20people%2C%20especially%20compared%20to%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20animal%20spirits%20are%20stirring%20in%20Japan%20is%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fjapanese-yen-faces-pressure-as-officials-maintain-accommodative-stance-1033208969%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyen%20has%20been%20getting%20crushed%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20other%20major%20currencies%20since%202022.%20As%20a%20country's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvisit-japan-economy-weak-yen-dollar-foreign-exchange-rate-tourism-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrency%20becomes%20cheaper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20its%20exports%20become%20more%20attractive%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20which%20helps%20explain%20why%20Japan's%20exports%20hit%20a%20record%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20and%20makes%20corporations%20that%20depend%20on%20exports%20look%20as%20if%20they%20have%20healthier%20balance%20sheets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20has%20made%20Japan%20attractive%20for%20foreign%20investors%2C%20and%20the%20stock%20market%20has%20done%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Koo%20said.%20But%20a%20weaker%20yen%20reduces%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20those%20using%20it%20domestically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20average%20Japanese%20people%20living%20in%20Japan%2C%20this%20has%20not%20been%20great%20news%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20being%20said%20outside%20Japan%20and%20how%20it%20feels%20inside%20are%20very%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETokyo%20knows%20it's%20not%20out%20of%20the%20woods%20yet%2C%20but%20economists%20largely%20agree%20that%20early%20this%20year%20was%20the%20time%20for%20Japan%20to%20strike%20%E2%80%94%20to%20pull%20itself%20out%20of%20negative%20interest%20rates%2C%20even%20if%20the%20economy%20is%20still%20finding%20its%20footing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInitially%20driven%20by%20cost-push%20factors%2C%20inflation%20is%20becoming%20demand-driven%20with%20the%20output%20gap%20closed%20and%20labor%20shortages%20intensifying%2C%26quot%3B%20researchers%20at%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20report.%20The%20biggest%20danger%2C%20they%20said%2C%20is%20that%20inflation%20has%20eaten%20up%20what%20little%20growth%20the%20country%20has.%20Luckily%2C%20though%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20global%20economy%20seems%20like%20it's%20in%20shape%20to%20support%20the%20country%20by%20buying%20Japanese%20goods%20and%20mobbing%20the%20country%20with%20a%20record%20number%20of%20tourists.%20That%20all%20must%20hold%20if%20we're%20to%20see%20Japan%20close%20the%20chapter%20on%20its%20economic%20fall%20from%20grace.%20And%20so%2C%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20Japan's%20most%20arduous%20phase%20of%20debt%20repayment%2C%20as%20companies%20looked%20healthier%20and%20the%20stock%20market%20much%20cheaper%20thanks%20to%20the%20currency%2C%20the%20world%20stepped%20in%20with%20more%20cash.%20None%20of%20it%20was%20a%20pretty%20process%2C%20but%20rest