inst%20a%20deflationary%20shock.%20Early%20efforts%20to%20stimulate%20were%20wishy-washy.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20generous%20fiscal%20package%20in%201995%20was%20countered%20with%20austerity%20in%201996%20and%201997%2C%20according%20to%20analysts%20from%20the%20Peterson%20Institute.%20It%20took%20years%20for%20policymakers%20to%20get%20their%20mix%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chinese%20are%20talking%20about%20it%20every%20day%2C%20they%20understand%20what%20kind%20of%20disease%20they%20contracted%2C%26quot%3B%20Koo%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhether%20that%20translates%20into%20a%20speedy%2C%20sufficient%2C%20and%20sustained%20stimulus%2C%20we%20haven't%20got%20there%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20took%20Japan%20years%20to%20come%20around%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20stimulus%2C%20China%20may%20never%20get%20there.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jiinping-future-tech-global-economy-semiconductors-military-failing-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EXi%20Jinping%20has%20shown%20few%20signs%3C%2Fa%3E%20he's%20willing%20to%20rain%20money%20down%20on%20the%20country's%20starved%20local%20governments%20or%20even%20on%20households%20to%20spur%20consumption.%20He%20doesn't%20really%20believe%20in%20handing%20money%20to%20consumers%20to%20let%20them%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%20with%20it.%20Instead%2C%20Xi's%20solution%20is%20to%20get%20China's%20monumental%20manufacturing%20machine%20to%20make%20higher-value%20goods.%20This%20continues%20the%20state's%20control%20over%20the%20economy%20since%20the%20state%20directs%20banks%20where%20to%20lend%20and%2C%20in%20Xi's%20opinion%2C%20sets%20China%20up%20to%20have%20the%20kind%20of%20economy%20that%20would%20rival%20other%20world%20powers.%20So%20Beijing%20is%20going%20all%20in%20on%20building%20the%20hard%20goods%20of%20the%20future%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-crush-tesla-elon-musk-american-ev-industry-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectric%20vehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20semiconductors%2C%20cellphones%2C%20computer%20screens.%20He%20wants%20Chinese%20companies%20to%20buy%20all%20those%20things%20from%20Chinese%20manufacturers%20as%20well%2C%20creating%20an%20ecosystem%20of%20technology%20that%20would%20dominate%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Xi%20wants%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20to%20buy%20these%20goods%20from%20that%20ecosystem.%20This%20is%20where%20trade%20conflict%20comes%20in.%20The%20first%20time%20China%20became%20a%20manufacturing%20juggernaut%2C%20in%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20the%20world%20embraced%20it.%20Policymakers%20thought%20that%20integrating%20China%20into%20the%20global%20economy%20would%20make%20it%20a%20more%20open%20society%20and%20that%20the%20wins%20for%20some%20US%20companies%20would%20outweigh%20the%20downsides%20for%20others.%20But%20we've%20found%20that%20wasn't%20the%20case.%20Instead%2C%20the%20world%20was%20hit%20by%20what%20economists%20now%20call%20the%20%26quot%3BChina%20shock%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20stripped%20the%20US%20of%20its%20manufacturing%20base%20and%20left%20whole%20communities%20without%20good%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%20experience%2C%20any%20whiff%20of%20a%20new%20China%20shock%20will%20almost%20certainly%20result%20in%20the%20world%20pushing%20back.%20Policymakers%20are%20unwilling%20to%20allow%20even%20more%20crucial%20productions%20and%20jobs%20to%20be%20shipped%20off%20and%20out%2C%20leaving%20angry%20voters%20and%20instability%20behind.%20Japan's%20leaders%20mostly%20ignored%20nationalist%20hard-liners%20who%20were%20angry%20at%20the%20US%20in%20the%201990s%20and%20focused%20on%20having%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20the%20US%2C%20as%20it%20needed%20the%20richest%20country%20in%20the%20world%20to%20buy%20its%20goods.%20China%20is%20taking%20a%20different%20tack%3A%20Even%20as%20Xi%20invites%20US%20leaders%20to%20China%20to%20talk%20about%20how%20open%20the%20country%20is%2C%20American%20brands%20are%20getting%20walloped%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-hiding-bad-data-economy-debt-real-estate-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20offices%20have%20been%20raided%20by%20Chinese%20officials%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20financial%20firms%20and%20consultancies%20are%20moving%20out%20of%20China.%20Not%20even%20the%20Chinese%20stock%20market's%20veritable%20collapse%20over%20the%20past%20few%20months%20interests%20investors%2C%20with%20Goldman%20Sachs%20warning%20clients%20to%20stay%20away.%20There's%20cheap%2C%20and%20then%20there's%20dangerous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20these%20adversarial%20circumstances%2C%20it's%20unclear%20how%20much%20the%20world%20will%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20what%20China%20is%20selling%20at%20any%20price.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20Beijing's%20biggest%20stumbling%20blocks.%20Tokyo%20was%20able%20to%20pull%20itself%20off%20the%20mat%20in%20part%20because%20when%20the%20yen%20fell%2C%20the%20world%20was%20OK%20with%20that.%20Japan%2C%20after%20shutting%20down%20nuclear%20plants%2C%20started%20importing%20energy%2C%20and%20there%20was%20less%20of%20a%20trade%20imbalance%20between%20it%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20China's%20balance%20of%20trade%20is%20still%20skewed%20toward%20exports%2C%20which%20means%20if%20the%20yuan%20falls%2C%20its%20goods%20get%20cheaper%20and%20can%20flood%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20imagine%20the%20screeching%20from%20Washington%20if%20there's%20even%20a%20hint%20that%20Beijing%20is%20allowing%20the%20yuan%20to%20depreciate%20in%20order%20to%20sell%20us%20more%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20without%20a%20currency%20war%20with%20Beijing%2C%20the%20world%20is%20building%20defenses%20against%20another%20wave%20of%20Chinese%20goods.%20Bras%C3%ADlia%20just%20launched%20an%20antidumping%20investigation%20into%20whether%20China%20is%20flooding%20Brazil%20with%20cheap%20goods.%20Turkey%20recently%20tightened%20regulation