A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-sell-house-right-now-austin-texas-market-selling-tips-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esold%20our%20starter%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-california-austin-texas-10-things-i-wish-i-knew-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAustin%2C%20Texas%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20are%20now%20in%20the%20market%20for%20a%20new%20house%20in%20a%20different%20part%20of%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-mortgage-refinance-rates-today-friday-29-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emortgage%20interest%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20still%20close%20to%207%25%2C%20alternative%20mortgages%20like%20adjustable-rate%20loans%20and%20mortgages%20with%20shorter%20maturities%20are%20gaining%20in%20popularity.%20However%2C%20after%20researching%20and%20talking%20to%20some%20experts%2C%20the%20pros%20for%20those%20loans%20don't%20outweigh%20the%20costs%2C%20and%20the%20classic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-fixed-rate-mortgage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efixed-rate%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20still%20the%20best%20option%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20beauty%20of%20the%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20is%20that%20it%20offers%20certainty%20in%20an%20uncertain%20world.%20With%20a%20fixed%20rate%2C%20your%20interest%20rate%20won't%20change%2C%20and%20you%20will%20always%20have%20the%20same%20monthly%20payment%20no%20matter%20what%20happens%20to%20rates%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20we%20are%20staying%20away%20from%20alternative%20mortgage%20types%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20homebuyers%20want%20%E2%80%94%20or%20need%20%E2%80%94%20their%20monthly%20mortgage%20payment%20to%20be%20as%20low%20as%20possible%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20long-term%20costs.%20However%2C%20we%20are%20lucky%20enough%20to%20be%20in%20a%20situation%20that%20allows%20us%20to%20be%20picky%2C%20and%20alternative%20mortgages%20are%20just%20not%20worth%20it%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20common%20of%20the%20alternative%20mortgage%20types%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fadjustable-rate-mortgage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadjustable-rate%20mortgage%20(ARM)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20especially%20appealing%20when%20interest%20rates%20are%20higher.%20ARMs%20still%20only%20represent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ffinance%2Fadjustable-rate-mortgage-interest-rates-86086ac5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E7%25%20of%20all%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20that%20rate%20has%20doubled%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years%20as%20interest%20rates%20rose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20ARM%2C%20you%20are%20locked%20into%20a%20lower%20rate%20for%20a%20set%20number%20of%20years%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20loan%2C%20and%20then%20the%20interest%20rate%20typically%20adjusts%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20year%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20rate%20at%20the%20time.%20The%20upside%20is%20lower%20payments%20initially%20and%20potentially%20later%20on%20if%20rates%20fall%2C%20but%20the%20downside%20is%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20if%20rates%20go%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20ARM%20might%20be%20a%20good%20option%20if%20you%20know%20you%20will%20sell%20the%20house%20before%20the%20adjustable%20rates%20kick%20in.%20That%20was%20the%20recommendation%20from%20Sarah%20Alvarez%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20mortgage%20banking%20at%20William%20Raveis%20Mortgage%2C%20for%20somebody%20planning%20to%20live%20in%20a%20house%20for%20five%20or%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20scenario%2C%20I%20would%20strongly%20recommend%20considering%20a%207-year%20adjustable%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20Alvarez%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20incentivized%20with%20a%20lower%20rate%20and%20will%20be%20paying%20off%20the%20mortgage%20before%20the%20rate%20leaves%20its%20fixed%20period.%20In%20this%20elevated%20rate%20market%2C%20it%20is%20best%20to%20focus%20on%20keeping%20the%20monthly%20payments%20low.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20both%20of%20our%20daughters%20entering%20high%20school%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years%2C%20there%20is%20a%20good%20chance%20we%20will%20look%20to%20downsize%20or%20move%20in%20the%20next%20seven%20or%20eight%20years%2C%20but%20that%20is%20not%20guaranteed%20and%20may%20depend%20on%20what%20the%20housing%20market%20looks%20like%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Austin%20skyline%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a80bf3dcdb354a9858442a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221873%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAustin%2C%20the%20home%20of%20the%20author.%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Bell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20problem%20with%20the%20ARM%20is%20that%20mortgage%20interest%20rates%20typically%20follow%20the%20rates%20for%20Treasury%20bonds%2C%20with%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%20following%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fmortgage-rate-climbs-us-housing-market-boom-treasury-yields-economy-2021-3-1030155272%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10-year%20Treasury%20yield%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20initial%20rate%20on%20ARMs%20following%20the%20rates%20of%20shorter%20notes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fadjustable-rate-mortgage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20the%201-year%20Treasury%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20the%20rates%20on%20short-term%20Treasuries%20are%20higher%20than%20long-term%20bonds%2C%20a%20phenomenon%20known%20as%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyield-curve-inversion-explained-what-it-is-what-it-means-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einverted%20yield%20curve%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20introductory%20interest%20rate%20on%20an%20ARM%20based%20on%20those%20short-term%20Treasury%20rates%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emight%20be%20only%20slightly%20better%20than%20the%20more%20predictable%20fixed-rate%20loans%20that%20rely%20on%20the%20long-term%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ffinance%2Fadjustable-rate-mortgage-interest-rates-86086ac5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EARM's%20interest%20rate%20can%20be%20higher%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20Optimal%20Blue%2C%20a%20mortgage%20data%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ffinance%2Fadjustable-rate-mortgage-interest-rates-86086ac5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evia%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20average%20initial%20rate%20for%20an%20ARM%20in%20which%20the%20first%20five%20years%20are%20fixed%20was%207.04%25%20in%20December.%20The%20average%20rate%20for%20a%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20that%20month%20was%206.86%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInterest-only%20mortgages%20feel%20too%20expensive%20and%20too%20risky%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20form%20of%20home%20financing%20that%20is%20gaining%20in%20popularity%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenrys-risky-unusual-interest-only-mortgage-loan-home-prices-soar-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest-only%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20interest-only%20mortgage%2C%20the%20buyer%20doesn't%20pay%20a%20monthly%20amount%20against%20the%20loan's%20principal%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20loan%20term%20but%20instead%20pays%20only%20the%20monthly%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20initial%20monthly%20payments%20are%20much%20lower%2C%20the%20principal%20is%20not%20being%20paid%20down%2C%20so%20the%20owner%20is%20only%20gaining%20equity%20from%20changes%20to%20the%20value%20of%20the%20initial%20down%20payment%20amount%20and%20not%20from%20reducing%20the%20amount%20the%20bank%20can%20claim%2C%20with%20a%20greater%20risk%20of%20losing%20equity%20if%20house%20values%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20borrower%20is%20adding%20a%20considerable%20amount%20to%20the%20total%20cost%20of%20the%20house%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20interest%20being%20paid%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBuying%20discount%20points%20is%20popular%20but%20may%20not%20be%20worth%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20common%20way%20to%20lower%20mortgage%20payments%20is%20with%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fmore-buyers-are-purchasing-mortgage-points-as-a-way-to-ease-monthly-costs-1032263170%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscount%20points%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20the%20buyer%20pays%20a%20lender%20at%20closing%20to%20lower%20the%20interest%20rate%2C%20with%20one%20point%20equal%20to%201%25%20of%20the%20loan%20amount%20and%20each%20point%20typically%20lowering%20the%20rate%20by%200.25%25.%20But%20it%20turns%20out%20even%20these%20are%20often%20not%20worth%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fresearch%2Fforecast%2F20240122-us-economy-continues-expand%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Freddie%20Mac%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2059%25%20of%20borrowers%20used%20points%20to%20lower%20their%20interest%20rate%20in%202023%2C%20up%20from%2031%25%20in%202021.%20And%20yet%2C%20according%20to%20their%20research%2C%20the%20average%20interest%20rate%20in%202023%20for%20those%20who%20purchased%20points%20was%206.61%25%20in%202023%2C%20only%20slightly%20better%20than%20the%206.69%25%20average%20rate%20for%20those%20who%20did%20not%20buy%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20shows%20that%20the%20pre-discount%20rate%20was%20higher%20for%20people%20who%20purchased%20points%20and%20could%20indicate%20that%20lenders%20view%20buyers%20seeking%20to%20lower%20their%20monthly%20payments%20as%20riskier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20consults%20with%20lender%20at%20office%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cfbf0ef533b039a884d3b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBuying%20points%20from%20a%20lender%20may%20be%20more%20costly%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20%3Cp%3EFG%20Trade%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20do%20receive%20a%20lower%20rate%20by%20buying%20points%2C%20it%20may%20only%20be%20beneficial%20if%20you%20plan%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fadvisor%2Fmortgages%2Fdiscount-points-may-not-be-worth-it-says-freddie-mac%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estay%20in%20the%20house%20for%20a%20long%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20long%20enough%20to%20save%20more%20money%20on%20interest%20than%20the%20amount%20spent%20lowering%20the%20rate.%20However%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fresearch-and-statistics%2Fquick-real-estate-statistics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Association%20of%20Realtors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20typical%20homeowner%20only%20stays%20in%20their%20house%20for%20eight%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20may%20only%20own%20our%20new%20house%20for%20less%20than%2010%20years%2C%20so%20buying%20discount%20points%20could%20cost%20us%20more%20on%20our%20next%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESticking%20with%20the%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20after%20all%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20no%20risk%20of%20the%20rate%20rising%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20lower%20your%20monthly%20mortgage%20payment%20with%20a%20fixed-rate%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20case%2C%20we'll%20likely%20be%20able%20to%20put%20a%20larger%20percentage%20down%20than%20when%20we%20bought%20our%20first%20house%20and%20interest%20rates%20were%20much%20less%20of%20a%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20may%20also%20choose%20to%20go%20with%20a%2030-year%20loan%20at%20first%20and%20then%20refinance%20down%20the%20road%20into%20our%20preferred%2015-year%20mortgage.%20This%20way%2C%20we%20can%20get%20a%20lower%20monthly%20payment%20initially%20without%20taking%20too%20much%20of%20a%20hit%20on%20the%20interest%20we%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20option%20for%20people%20who%20want%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20is%20to%20wait%20and%20hope%20that%20interest%20rates%20fall.%20However%2C%20that%20is%20also%20risky%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-cant-millennials-buy-homes-first-time-buyers-mortgage-rates-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehouse%20prices%20have%20remained%20steady%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20are%20even%20still%20rising%20in%20some%20places.%20Any%20gain%20somebody%20might%20get%20with%20a%20lower%20interest%20rate%20might%20be%20offset%20by%20paying%20more%20for%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20alternatives%20available%20to%20homebuyers%20looking%20to%20lower%20their%20monthly%20mortgage%20payments.%20However%2C%20those%20benefits%20are%20often%20small%20and%20end%20up%20costing%20more%20overall.%20So%2C%20we%20will%20be%20sticking%20with%20a%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20and%20shopping%20around%20for%20the%20best%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDid%20you%20use%20an%20alternative%20mortgage%20type%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20in%20recent%20years%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acgaines%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ecgaines%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffixed-rate-mortgages-better-adjustable-discount-points-interest-rate-savings-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711876921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6606e3e51caec1275a6ae7c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider