igcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELandfills%20are%20a%20large%20driver%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%20due%20to%20their%20high%20methane%20leaks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20recent%20study%20found%20methane%20emissions%20from%20landfills%20were%2040%25%20higher%20than%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAdvanced%20methods%20like%20remote%20sensing%20can%20help%20detect%20and%20fix%20landfill%20methane%20leaks%20faster.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERotting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsell-by-best-before-dates-mean-nothing-create-food-waste-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20scraps%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20waste%20that%20piles%20up%20in%20landfills%20across%20the%20country%20are%20a%20larger%20driver%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%20than%20previously%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMethane%20leaks%20from%20landfills%20were%2C%20on%20average%2C%2040%25%20higher%20than%20what's%20been%20reported%20to%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.adi7735%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20flew%20airplanes%20over%20more%20than%20200%20active%20landfills%20in%20the%20US%2C%20or%20about%2020%25%20of%20the%20total%2C%20between%202018%20and%202022%20in%20the%20largest%20assessment%20of%20the%20industry%20to%20date.%20Spectrometers%20detected%20methane%20plumes%20at%20more%20than%20half%20of%20those%20landfills%2C%20with%20most%20leaking%20the%20gas%20for%20months%2C%20if%20not%20years.%20The%20plumes%20were%20more%20persistent%20than%20those%20found%20in%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20sector%2C%20which%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcop28-un-climate-conference-oil-and-gas-methane-emissions-satellites-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecome%20under%20increasing%20scrutiny%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20scientists%20say%20that%20slashing%20methane%20emissions%20from%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20landfills%2C%20and%20livestock%20is%20one%20of%20the%20fastest%20ways%20to%20slow%20the%20climate%20crisis%20because%20the%20gas%20has%2080%20times%20the%20warming%20power%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20over%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELandfills%20are%20considered%20the%20third-largest%20source%20of%20human-caused%20methane%20emissions%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20behind%20agriculture%20and%20oil%20and%20gas.%20But%20estimates%20for%20landfills%20are%20based%20on%20computer%20models%20and%20not%20actual%20observations%2C%20said%20Dan%20Cusworth%2C%20project%20scientist%20at%20Carbon%20Mapper%20and%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBridging%20that%20gap%20is%20critical%2C%26quot%3B%20Cusworth%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20help%20mitigate%20emissions%20and%20also%20validate%20whether%20various%20climate%20efforts%20are%20having%20the%20intended%20impacts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20infrared%20imaging%20spectrometer%20inside%20an%20airplane.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6606f0521caec1275a6af04c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAirplanes%20with%20an%20infrared%20imaging%20spectrometer%20measure%20methane%20plumes.%3Cp%3EArizona%20State%20University%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELandfill%20workers%20currently%20do%20walking%20surveys%20with%20handheld%20sensors%20to%20detect%20methane%20hot%20spots.%20But%20that%20method%20is%20prone%20to%20error%20and%20only%20required%20once%20a%20quarter%2C%20Cusworth%20said.%20Waste%20sites%20can%20also%20span%20thousands%20of%20acres%20and%20can%20be%20dangerous%20to%20traverse%2C%20especially%20in%20areas%20where%20trash%20is%20being%20dumped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20advanced%20methods%2C%20like%20remote%20sensing%20from%20satellites%2C%20aircraft%2C%20and%20drones%2C%20can%20deliver%20a%20more%20accurate%20picture%20of%20the%20methane%20problem%20at%20landfills.%20The%20sources%20of%20emissions%20vary.%20Many%20large%20landfills%20capture%20methane%20gas%20so%20it%20can%20be%20reused%20as%20energy%2C%20but%20that%20infrastructure%20can%20leak.%20When%20food%20waste%20decomposes%2C%20it%20releases%20the%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20timely%20detection%20can%20help%20landfill%20operators%20fix%20leaks%20faster%2C%20benefiting%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarbon%20Mapper%20notified%20environmental%20regulators%20in%20Southern%20California%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.paenvironmentdigest.com%2Fnewsletter%2Fdefault.asp%3FNewsletterArticleID%3D57582%26SubjectID%3D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPennsylvania%20about%20the%20methane%20leaks%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20detected.%20In%20response%2C%20officials%20notified%20landfill%20operators%20so%20they%20could%20reduce%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarbon%20Mapper%20aims%20to%20launch%20a%20constellation%20of%20satellites%20measuring%20methane%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20in%20partnership%20with%20NASA%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%2C%20the%20climate%20nonprofit%20RMI%2C%20and%20others.%20The%20methane%20satellite%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20launched%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20goal%20is%20to%20launch%20many%20of%20these%20satellites%20so%20we%20can%20capture%20a%20large%20swath%20of%20global%20landfill%20sites%2C%20as%20well%20as%20oil%20and%20gas%20sites%2C%20to%20really%20identify%20the%20point-source%2C%20facility%20scale%20emissions%2C%26quot%3B%20Cusworth%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Environmental%20Defense%20Fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-launches-methanesat-track-global-methane-leaks-03-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilarly%20launched%20a%20methane%20satellite%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Space%20X%20in%20March%20that%20will%20police%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandfills-leaking-more-methane-than-previously-known-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711876621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6606f0873f923f7dab02b27d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandfills-leaking-more-methane-than-previously-known-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Landfills%20are%20thought%20to%20be%20the%20third-largest%20source%20of%20methane%20emissions%20in%20the%20US.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandfills-leaking-more-methane-than-previously-known-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22McSki%20in%20Sweden%20is%20McDonald's%20only%20ski-thru%20restaurant%2C%20where%20you%20can%20grab%20a%20Big%20Mac%20to%20take%20down%20the%20slopes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20the%20McSki%20location%20in%20S%C3%A4len%2C%20Sweden%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f9bdd44af076d3cf91ac34%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMcDonald's%20Ski-Thru%20restaurant%20in%20Sweden.%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20Sverige%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMcDonald's%20has%20just%20one%20McSki%2C%20or%20Ski-Thru%2C%20located%20in%20one%20of%20Sweden's%20biggest%20resorts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHunger%20skiers%20can%20stop%20for%20hot%20chocolates%2C%20Big%20Macs%2C%20and%20doughnuts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20offers%20table%20service%2C%20or%20you%20can%20ski%20off%20with%20your%20food.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%20it's%20easy%20to%20get%20a%20Big%20Mac%20delivered%20to%20your%20h