2C%20his%20daughters%20are%20struggling%20to%20budget%20for%20college.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20lack%20of%20clarity%20has%20Scordo%20nervous%20he'll%20be%20in%20a%20time%20crunch%20to%20find%20out%20how%20to%20afford%20tuition.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAntonio%20Scordo%2C%2050%2C%20wants%20to%20help%20his%20two%20daughters%20determine%20their%20budgets%20for%20college.%20The%20only%20problem%3A%20he%20has%20no%20idea%20how%20much%20college%20will%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20already%20sent%20his%20son%20through%20college%2C%20Scordo%20was%20familiar%20with%20the%20Free%20Application%20for%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffafsa-how-to-get-college-financial-aid-chaotic-rollout-delays-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eor%20FAFSA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20process%20%E2%80%94%20but%20this%20year%20has%20brought%20a%20host%20of%20new%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden's%20Education%20Department%20announced%20last%20year%20that%20it%20would%20be%20overhauling%20FAFSA%20applications%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-more-financial-aid-student-loans-fafsa-update-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20them%20more%20streamlined%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20students%20and%20families%2C%20but%20the%20overhaul%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffafsa-why-parents-students-have-to-wait-financial-aid-awards-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eled%20to%20delays%20and%20errors%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20department%20began%20sending%20students'%20applications%20to%20schools%20in%20early%20March%2C%20which%20is%20two%20months%20delayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20that%20not%20only%20would%20schools%20have%20a%20shortened%20timeframe%20to%20devise%20financial%20aid%20packages%2C%20but%20families%20would%20also%20be%20in%20a%20time%20crunch%20to%20evaluate%20the%20rewards%20they%20receive%20and%20determine%20which%20college%20is%20best%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScordo%20said%20these%20delays%20have%20placed%20immense%20pressure%20on%20himself%20and%20his%20daughters%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20information%20they%20need%20to%20plan%20for%20college%20this%20fall%2C%20and%20it's%20keeping%20them%20from%20applying%20for%20other%20forms%20of%20financial%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20even%20really%20start%20applying%20for%20private%20loans%20and%20trying%20to%20compare%20and%20contrast%20better%20private%20student%20loans%20between%20different%20companies%20because%20we%20do%20want%20to%20know%20how%20much%20the%20college%20is%20going%20to%20cost%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20apply%20for%20too%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20Scordo%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20also%20don't%20want%20to%20apply%20for%20not%20enough%20because%20then%20you're%20scrambling%20to%20try%20to%20find%20money%20at%20the%20last%20minute.%20So%20it's%20a%20lot%20of%20stress%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20feature%20of%20FAFSA%20that%20Scordo%20is%20waiting%20for%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20corrections%20to%20his%20daughters'%20applications.%20One%20of%20his%20daughters%20is%20seeking%20to%20transfer%20schools%2C%20and%20she's%20been%20unable%20to%20add%20a%20school%20that%20offers%20her%20desired%20program%20to%20the%20application.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffsapartners.ed.gov%2Fknowledge-center%2Flibrary%2Felectronic-announcements%2F2024-03-25%2Fupdate-2024-25-fafsa-processing%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520ability%2520for%2520students%2520to%2Cthe%2520first%2520half%2520of%2520April.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20corrections%20and%20updates%20will%20not%20become%20available%20until%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20half%20of%20April.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%20the%20FAFSA%20dashboard%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereviewed%20by%20BI%2C%20the%20notice%20regarding%20corrections%20for%20one%20of%20Scordo's%20daughters%20states%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20expect%20that%20online%20corrections%20will%20be%20available%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20you%20can%20review%20your%20responses%20and%20see%20your%20eligibility%20information.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20his%20daughter%20will%20have%20to%20keep%20waiting%20to%20learn%20if%20she%20can%20transfer%20to%20her%20desired%20program.%20The%20delays%20also%20don't%20help%20his%20other%20daughter%20%E2%80%94%20an%20incoming%20freshman%20who%20has%20already%20committed%20to%20her%20program.%20Since%20she%20doesn't%20know%20how%20much%20financial%20aid%20she'll%20receive%2C%20Scordo%20said%20she's%20applying%20%26quot%3Blike%20crazy%26quot%3B%20for%20scholarships%2C%20but%20that's%20even%20been%20a%20challenge%20because%20many%20of%20the%20scholarship%20forms%20require%20information%20on%20how%20much%20the%20school%20costs%2C%20including%20how%20much%20financial%20aid%20the%20applicant%20is%20receiving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI%20on%20whether%20it's%20confident%20it%20can%20adhere%20to%20its%20timeline%20to%20allow%20students%20to%20make%20corrections%20to%20their%20applications.%20A%20spokesperson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F03%2F22%2Fcardona-federal-student-aid-blame-00148547%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%3C%2Fa%3E%20Politico%20that%20Education%20Sec.%20Miguel%20Cardona%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20crystal%20clear%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Department%20is%20working%20tirelessly%20to%20ensure%20every%20student%20who%20qualifies%20for%20aid%20can%20fill%20out%20a%20FAFSA%20form%20with%20ease%20and%20access%20the%20aid%20they%20need%20to%20attain%20their%20higher%20education%20goals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20chaotic%20FAFSA%20rollout%20hasn't%20inspired%20confidence%20in%20Scordo%2C%20who%20said%20he%20thinks%20it's%20%26quot%3Bticking%20off%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20out%20there%20that%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20their%20kids%20into%20college.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20they%20could%20have%20done%20it%20a%20lot%20smoother%2C%26quot%3B%20Scordo%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20should%20have%20worked%20it%20out.%20This%20was%20a%20horrible%20rollout.%20I%20mean%2C%20can%20you%20imagine%20if%20Microsoft%20rolled%20a%20product%20out%20that%20was%20this%20bad%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20paying%20until%20I'm%20dead'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20is%20Scordo%20struggling%20to%20budget%20for%20his%20kids'%20education%2C%20but%20he%20also%20has%20student%20loans%20of%20his%20own.%20To%20help%20pay%20for%20his%20son%20and%20one%20of%20his%20daughter's%20schools%2C%20he%20took%20out%20nearly%20%2450%2C000%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-single-mom-student-debt-plus-loans-set-to-double-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparent%20PLUS%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20per%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20BI.%20These%20are%20loans%20a%20parent%20can%20take%20out%20to%20cover%20up%20to%20the%20full%20cost%20of%20attendance%20at%20their%20kid's%20school.%20They%20also%20have%20the%20highest%20interest%20rate%20of%20all%20federal%20loans%2C%20making%20them%20difficult%20to%20pay%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20finished%20paying%20off%20their%20own%20student%20loans%20right%20before%20their%20son%20went%20into%20college%2C%20and%20given%20the%20balance%20he%20already%20has%20in%20PLUS%20loans%2C%20he's%20trying%20to%20avoid%20taking%20out%20more%20for%20his%20daughters.%20But%20not%20knowing%20how%20much%20their%20tuition%20will%20be%20complicates%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20help%20my%20kids%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20working%20until%20I'm%2080%2C%26quot%3B%20Scordo%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20paying%20until%20I'm%20dead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20FAFSA%20delays%2C%20some%20colleges%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffafsa-how-to-get-college-financial-aid-chaotic-rollout-delays-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epushed%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20commitment%20deadlines%2C%20typically%20May%201%2C%20to%20later%20in%20May%2C%20allowing%20students%20more%20time%20to%20evaluate%20their%20financial%20aid%20packages.%20But%20errors%20keep%20arising%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Education%20Department%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffsapartners.ed.gov%2Fknowledge-center%2Flibrary%2Felectronic-announcements%2F2024-03-22%2Fupdate-2024-25-fafsa-institutional-student-information-record-isir-delivery%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20detected%20mistakes%20calculating%20aid%20for%20nearly%20200%2C000%20applicants%2C%20likely%20resulting%20in%20further%20delays%20for%20final%20reward%20packages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECardona%20also%20recently%20sent%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.ed.gov%2Fpolicy%2Fgen%2Fguid%2Fsecletter%2F240326.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20governors%20asking%20them%20to%20encourage%20schools%20in%20their%20states%20to%20extend%20their%20commitment%20deadlines%20and%20work%20with%20the%20schools%20to%20ensure%20they%20have%20the%20resources%20they%20need%20to%20efficiently%20calculate%20students'%20rewards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20Scordo%20and%20his%20daughters%20are%20waiting%20for%20the%20option%20to%20update%20their%20applications%2C%20but%20they'll%20remain%20in%20limbo%20until%20they%20can%20find%20out%20how%20much%20financial%20aid%20they're%20getting%20and%20whether%20they%20can%20afford%20to%20attend%20their%20desired%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20bad%20for%20other%20parents%20that%20are%20going%20through%20this%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Scordo%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20has%20been%20a%20debacle%20all%20the%20way%20from%20the%20top%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20way%20it's%20been%20administered.%20If%20I%20were%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20company%20that%20did%20this%2C%20I%20would%20be%20looking%20at%20who's%20responsible%2C%20and%20they%20would%20probably%20be%20fired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdad-paying-for-college-fafsa-issues-parent-plus-student-loans-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711876021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66047f4416bde8d4ead2d199%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdad-paying-for-college-fafsa-issues-parent-plus-student-loans-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20top%20of%20the%20confusing%20and%20delayed%20FAFSA%20process%20this%20year%2C%20Antonio%20Scordo%20is%20also%20dealing%20with%20parent%20PLUS%20student%20loans%20of%20his%20own.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdad-paying-for-college-fafsa-issues-parent-plus-student-loans-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20Swede%20who%20used%20to%20work%20with%20Americans.%20These%20are%20the%20main%20differences%20I%20saw%20in%20our%20working%20cultures.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20with%20baby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660569953f923f7dab01f551%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECEO%20Sofia%20Brandt%20said%20Sweden's%20parental%20leave%20laws%20mean%20dads%20can%20play%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20their%20kids'%20lives.%20%3Cp%3EMaskot%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESofia%20Brandt%20used%20to%20work%20for%20Accenture%20before%20becoming%20a%20founder%20and%20lives%20in%20Gothenburg%2C%20Sweden.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBrandt%20shares%20the%20aspects%20of%20Swedish%20work%20culture%20that%20might%20surprise%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%C2%A0Swedes%20get%20480%20days%20of%20parental%20leave%20that%20can%20be%20split%20between%20couples%20and%C2%A0find%20bragging%20uncouth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Sofia%20Brandt%2C%20cofounder%20of%20the%20therapy%20app%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fallycouples.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAlly%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Gothenburg%2C%20Sweden.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20at%20Accenture%20for%20seven%20years%2C%20primarily%20with%20American%20and%20Swedish%20corporations%2C%20before%20founding%20my%20own%20startup%2C%20a%20therapy%20app%20called%20Ally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20at%20Accenture%2C%20I%20noticed%20a%20lot%20of%20differences%20between%20Swedish%20and%20American%20working%20styles.%20There%20are%20also%20aspects%20of%20working%20life%20in%20Sweden%20that%20I%20have%20observed%20as%20a%20founder%20that%20make%20life%20easier%20for%20parents%20and%20create%20better%20working%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20main%20aspects%20of%20working%20in%20Sweden%20that%20other%20cultures%20might%20find%20surprising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupport%20for%20working%20parents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Sweden%2C%20parental%20leave%20has%20become%20an%20incubator%20for%20new%20ideas%20and%20people%20often%20change%20career%20direction%20during%20their%20leave.%20You%20get%2016%20months%20off%20work%20to%20care%20for%20a%20new%20child%2C%20often%20at%20full%20pay%2C%20if%20your%20company%20tops%20up%20the%20government%20provision.%20You%20get%20480%20days%20of%20parental%20allowance%20shared%20between%20parents%20per%20child%20from%20the%20state-governed%20insurance%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20390%20days%2C%20you%20get%20around%2080%25%20of%20your%20salary.%20You%20get%20a%20smaller%20amount%20for%20the%20remaining%2090%20days%2C%20around%2015%20euros%20a%20day.%20That%20support%20gives%20people%20time%20to%20consider%20their%20careers%20and%20reflect%20on%20ideas%20while%20caring%20for%20their%20newborn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%2012%20months%20of%20maternity%20leave%20from%20Accenture%2C%20I%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20our%20startup.%20Alongside%20caring%20for%20my%20newborn%2C%20I%20had%20long%20stroller%20walks%20and%20other%20carved-out%20time%20spent%20thinking%20about%20my%20budding%20business%20idea%20and%20iterating%20with%20my%20fellow%20co-founders.%20Being%20on%20leave%20gives%20you%20time%20to%20think%20with%20some%20distance%20from%20everyday%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20been%20financially%20supported%20during%20my%20parental%20leave%20and%20as%20my%20children%20grow.%20As%20a%20startup%20founder%2C%20you're%20initially%20paid%20very%20little.%20We%20coped%20because%20of%20Sweden's%20financial%20provisions%20for%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subsidized%20childcare%20system%20means%20we%20pay%20less%20than%20%24125%20a%20month%20to%20have%20both%20kids%20at%20full-time%20day%20care%2C%20compared%20to%20our%20friends%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20who%20pay%20about%20%242%2C900%20monthly%20per%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESweden%20also%20has%C2%A0%26quot%3Bv%C3%A5rd%20av%20barn%26quot%3B%2C%20or%20VAB%2C%20a%20policy%20where%20you%20can%20take%20paid%20days%20off%20to%20stay%20home%20and%20care%20for%20your%20sick%20child.%20There's%20an%20open%20culture%20around%20it%2C%20too%2C%20with%20people%20saying%20they're%20VAB-ing%20in%20their%20out-of-office%20responses%20and%20Slack%20statuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFathers%20also%20have%20to%20take%20three%20months%20of%20parental%20leave%2C%20which%20is%20great%20because%20it%20pushes%20dads%20to%20take%20more%20of%20a%20front%20seat%20in%20their%20children's%20lives%20and%20gives%20working%20moms%20more%20flexibility.%20Out%20of%20the%20480%20days%2C%20at%20least%2090%20have%20to%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20parent%20who%20hasn't%20taken%20the%20majority.%20Most%20couples%20try%20to%20split%20it%2050%2F50%2C%20but%20you%20can%20split%20it%20however%20you%20like.%20This%20means%20that%20one%20parent%20can%20take%20390%20days%2C%20and%20the%20other%20takes%2090%20days%2C%20or%20you%20can%20split%20it%20in%20half%20or%20anywhere%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20I%20was%20about%20to%20have%20my%20second%20child.%20I'd%20been%20running%20Ally%20for%20several%20years%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20a%20good%20time%20to%20take%20my%20maternity%20leave.%20My%20husband%20did%20the%20first%20six%20months%2C%20and%20I%20took%20time%20off%20afterward.%20He%20got%20comments%2C%20mainly%20from%20older%20people%2C%20who%20thought%20it%20strange.%20But%20for%20us%2C%20it%20worked%20perfectly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHumble%20approach%20to%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20at%20Accenture%2C%20I%20noticed%20differences%20between%20Swedish%20and%20American%20working%20styles.%20In%20Sweden%2C%20work-life%20balance%20is%20important%2C%20and%20what%20you%20do%20in%20your%20free%20time%20plays%20a%20bigger%20part%20in%20your%20identity%2C%20whereas%20it's%20the%20opposite%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESweden%20has%20a%20built-in%20cultural%20code%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fworklife%2Farticle%2F20191008-jantelagen-why-swedes-wont-talk-about-wealth%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMany%2520cultural%2520commentators%2520agree%2520that%2520a%2520large%2520part%2520of%2520the%2520taboo%2520can%2520be%2520explained%2520by%2520a%2520deep%252Drooted%2520Nordic%2520code%2520called%2520Jantelagen%252C%2520which%2520promotes%2520the%2520idea%2520of%2520never%2520thinking%2520you%2520are%2520better%2520than%2520anyone%2520else%2520and%2520calling%2520out%2520those%2520who%2520break%2520this%2520norm.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bjantelagen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20everyone%20is%20considered%20equal.%20Humility%20is%20essential%2C%20and%20talking%20about%20money%20is%20generally%20off-limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20America%2C%20individual%20success%20is%20celebrated.%20You%20are%20loud%20about%20your%20wins%20and%20celebrate%20earning%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBragging%20in%20Sweden%20and%20exaggerating%20your%20achievements%20or%20being%20overly%20flashy%20is%20risky%2C%20as%20you%20may%20appear%20obnoxious%20or%20crude%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20wouldn't%20formally%20jeopardize%20your%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20recruiting%20employees%20in%20Sweden%2C%20you%20have%20to%20ask%20yourself%20whether%20the%20candidate%20is%20holding%20back%2C%20and%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20to%20push%20candidates%20to%20say%20what%20they've%20been%20doing%2C%20and%20with%20international%20recruiters%2C%20Swedes%20might%20lose%20out%20because%20they%20won't%20talk%20up%20their%20full%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20cofounders%20and%20I%20are%20struggling%20with%20%26quot%3Bjantelagen.%26quot%3B%20Our%20all-female%20founding%20team%20needs%20to%20pitch%20ourselves%20in%20this%20tough%20economic%20climate.%20There's%20a%20fine%20line%20between%20humility%20and%20ambition%2C%20and%20talking%20to%20international%20investors%20with%20our%20Swedish%20nature%20is%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFlat%20companies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20built%20Ally%20to%20be%20non-hierarchical%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20just%20a%20startup%20thing.%20In%20Sweden%2C%20companies%20have%20almost%20no%20hierarchy%2C%20and%20everyone%20has%20the%20right%20to%20speak%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20work%20as%20a%20team%20of%20individuals%2C%20and%20everybody%20is%20accountable.%20But%20you%20must%20get%20everybody%20on%20board%20to%20make%20a%20change%20or%20decision.%20It%20means%20putting%20a%20lot%20of%20trust%20in%20people%20to%20get%20things%20done%20independently.%20It%20also%20creates%20a%20strong%20individual%20responsibility%20toward%20a%20company's%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollective%20bargaining%2C%20another%20tenet%20of%20Swedish%20working%20culture%2C%20prioritizes%20employee%20needs%20and%20gives%20more%20power%20to%20the%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20are%20trade%20union%20members%2C%20and%20employers%20often%20encourage%20it.%20With%20the%20union%20comes%20greater%20worker%20power%20and%20expertise%20in%20negotiating%20pay%2C%20benefits%2C%20and%20hours%2C%20rather%20than%20having%20to%20fend%20for%20yourself%20and%20negotiate%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20seen%20it%20from%20both%20sides%2C%20many%20of%20these%20innately%20Swedish%20traits%20help%20build%20sustainable%20businesses%20over%20time%20and%20safeguard%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20employer%20and%20employee%20so%20everyone%20can%20work%20together%20positively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-culture-sweden-parental-leave-no-bragging-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711875901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660580051caec1275a6a4313%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-culture-sweden-parental-leave-no-bragging-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Working%20in%20Sweden%20comes%20with%20480%20days%20of%20parental%20leave%2C%20an%20aversion%20to%20bragging%20about%20your%20successes%20and%20more%20responsibility%20at%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Megan%20Carnegie)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-culture-sweden-parental-leave-no-bragging-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%