%20Accountability%20Project%20is%20meant%20to%C2%A0diminish%20the%20profession's%20culture%20of%20fear%20and%20silence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20review%20database%20launched%20this%20month%20and%20is%20available%20only%20to%20law%20students%20and%20recent%20grads.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20a%20workplace%20in%20a%20field%20with%20minimal%20regulation%20or%20oversight%2C%20with%20managers%20treated%20with%20reverence%20and%20respect%20by%20all%20manner%20of%20law%20enforcement.%20Managers%20whose%20job%20is%20to%20interpret%20the%20law%20and%20weigh%20in%20on%20matters%20of%20guilt%20or%20innocence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20imagine%20one%20of%20those%20managers%20harasses%20or%20belittles%20an%20employee%20%E2%80%94%20or%20worse%20%E2%80%94%20and%20with%20impunity%2C%20threatens%20their%20career%20if%20they%20complain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorney%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-pauline-newman-investigation-law-clerk-jobs-errands-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAliza%20Shatzman%3C%2Fa%3E%20knows%20exactly%20how%20it%20feels%2C%20and%20she's%20made%20it%20her%20mission%20to%20help%20prevent%20anyone%20else%20from%20having%20the%20same%20experience.%20That's%20why%2C%20after%20sharing%20her%20story%20in%20congressional%20testimony%20to%20lobby%20for%20more%20protections%20for%20clerks%20and%20other%20judiciary%20employees%2C%20she%20started%20the%20Legal%20Accountability%20Project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20month%2C%20LAP%20launched%20a%20new%20database%20for%20law%20clerks%20to%20leave%20reviews%20of%20their%20experiences%20working%20for%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclarence-thomas-clerks-brought-lobsters-rv-batteries-loyalties-nyt-scotus-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epowerful%20bosses%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20state%20and%20federal%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EJudges%20gone%20wild%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20local%20jurisdictions%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20judges%20nationwide%20conduct%20their%20business%20with%20little%20regulatory%20oversight.%20They%20are%20supervisors%20of%20both%20their%20courtrooms%20and%20the%20clerks%20they%20manage.%20Still%2C%20despite%20their%20tremendous%20authority%20and%20a%20long%20history%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclarence-thomas-troubles-point-to-scotus-accountability-issues-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabuses%20of%20power%20in%20the%20judiciary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20judges%20are%20all%20but%20immune%20from%20disciplinary%20action%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbankruptcy-judge-david-jones-resigns-texas-corizon-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emisconduct%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20formalize%20some%20of%20the%20informal%20resources%20and%20networks%20out%20there%20that%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20Shatzman%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20who%20said%20clerks%20%E2%80%94%20who%20are%20usually%20law%20students%20and%20recent%20graduates%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20their%20careers%20%E2%80%94%20often%20rely%20on%20word-of-mouth%20referrals%20and%20warnings%20about%20their%20prospective%20bosses%20to%20decide%20where%20to%20work.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20fear%20surrounding%20the%20judiciary%2C%20there's%20a%20real%20culture%20of%20silence%2C%20and%20so%20our%20resources%20and%20our%20work%20are%20aimed%20at%20combating%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20database%20collects%20both%20positive%20and%20negative%20evaluations%20from%20clerks%2C%20and%20it%20is%20protected%20from%20liability%20issues%20stemming%20from%20the%20reviews%20by%20a%20law%20known%20as%20Section%20230%2C%20which%20prevents%20sites%20like%20Yelp%20and%20Glassdoor%20from%20being%20held%20liable%20for%20the%20user-generated%20content%20hosted%20on%20their%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20could%20be%20two%20sides%20to%20any%20of%20these%20stories%2C%26quot%3B%20Judge%20Douglas%20Nazarian%2C%20a%20state%20appellate%20judge%20in%20Maryland%20who%20sits%20on%20LAP's%20board%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fdc-md-va%2F2024%2F02%2F25%2Flaw-clerks-rate-judges%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20database.%20%26quot%3BThe%20purpose%20is%20to%20democratize%20and%20improve%20the%20clerkship%20experience%2C%20not%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20get%20judges%20in%20trouble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAccountability%20born%20from%20congressional%20testimony%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShatzman%20said%20LAP's%20review%20database%20is%20the%20resource%20she%20wished%20existed%20when%20she%20was%20a%20student%20at%20Washington%20University%20in%20St.%20Louis%20School%20of%20Law%20applying%20for%20a%20clerkship%20and%20later%2C%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclarence-thomas-told-clerks-he-wants-to-make-liberals-miserable-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaw%20clerk%3C%2Fa%3E%20experiencing%20mistreatment%20and%20unsure%20where%20to%20turn%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%202022%20congressional%20testimony%20about%20the%20need%20for%20statutory%20change%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.house.gov%2Fmeetings%2FJU%2FJU03%2F20220317%2F114503%2FHHRG-117-JU03-20220317-SD005.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotect%20federal%20judiciary%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Shatzman%20said%20the%20judge%20she%20clerked%20for%20from%20August%202019%20until%20May%202020%20would%20call%20her%20names%2C%20describing%20her%20as%20%26quot%3Baggressive%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bnasty%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bdisappointment%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20berate%20her%20for%20what%20he%20described%20as%20her%20%26quot%3Bpersonality%20issues%26quot%3B%20when%20no%20one%20was%20around.%20Shatzman%20said%20the%20judge%20gave%20her%20unfavorable%20work%20assignments%2C%20regularly%20made%20her%20stay%20late%20in%20the%20office%20after%20her%20colleagues%20had%20left%20to%20yell%20at%20her%2C%20and%20ultimately%20terminated%20her%20clerkship%20early%2C%20saying%20she%20%26quot%3Blacked%20respect%26quot%3B%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20Shatzman%20clerked%20for%20has%20not%20made%20any%20public%20statement%20regarding%20her%20clerkship%20or%20complaint%20or%20his%20subsequent%20retirement.%20Emails%20from%20Business%20Insider%20seeking%20comment%20sent%20to%20accounts%20associated%20with%20the%20judge%20bounced%20back%2C%20and%20phone%20calls%20went%20unreturned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20didn't%20stop%20there.%20She%20testified%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20Congress%20that%20the%20judge%20she%20worked%20for%20later%20gave%20a%20prospective%20employer%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-this-tech-ceo-asks-for-a-negative-reference-2015-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegative%20reference%3C%2Fa%3E%20despite%20assuring%20Shatzman%20he'd%20be%20neutral%20if%20contacted%20about%20her%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20offer%20was%20revoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20not%20believe%20that%20one%20person%20could%20have%20such%20enormous%20power%20and%20influence%20over%20my%20career%20and%20reputation%2C%26quot%3B%20Shatzman%20testified%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20US%20Attorney's%20Office%2C%20where%20she'd%20been%20hired%2C%20would%20not%20disclose%20what%20the%20judge%20had%20said%20about%20her%2C%20even%20after%20she%20told%20them%20that%20she%20had%20been%20the%20victim%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiscrimination-at-work-women-all-ages-jobs-hiring-employer-bosses-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egender%20discrimination%20and%20harassment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20office%20refused%20to%20reconsider%20its%20position%2C%20and%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20damage%20had%20been%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuman%20resources%20for%20the%20courts%20told%20her%20nothing%20could%20be%20done%20because%20%26quot%3BHR%20doesn't%20regulate%20judges%2C%26quot%3B%20Shatzman%20testified.%20The%20federal%20judiciary%20is%20exempt%20from%20protections%20offered%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-rules-that-title-vii-applies-to-lgbtq-people-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETitle%20VII%20of%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20means%20employees%20like%20clerks%20can't%20sue%20if%20they%20experience%20employment%20discrimination%20based%20on%20race%20or%20sex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Shatzman%20submitted%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20Commission%20on%20Judicial%20Disabilities%20and%20Tenure%20about%20the%20judge's%20conduct%20toward%20her%2C%20the%20complaint%20was%20ultimately%20dismissed.%20According%20to%20disciplinary%20records%20reviewed%20by%20BI%2C%20the%20judge%20was%20later%20removed%20from%20the%20bench%20for%20unrelated%20conduct%20violations%20and%20health%20reasons%20in%20an%20%26quot%3Buncontested%20order%20of%20involuntary%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20whisper%20network%20legitimized%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20beginning%20to%20collect%20reviews%20in%202022%2C%20LAP%20has%20gathered%20over%20800%20surveys%20from%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-allison-greenfield-engoron-law-clerk-trump-fraud-trial-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaw%20clerks%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20their%20experiences%20working%20for%20state%20and%20federal%20judges%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShatzman%20personally%20vets%20each%20review.%20While%20reviews%20can%20be%20published%20to%20the%20database%20anonymously%2C%20she%20confirms%20the%20identity%20of%20each%20reviewer%20via%20their%20verified%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fis-law-school-worth-it%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaw%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20email%20addresses%20and%20work